Stephen Palmer is a British orienteer. He ran the third leg in Britain's silver medal winning relay team at the 1993 World Orienteering Championships. Palmer was also a member of the British relay team that won the Nordic Championships in 2001.
Palmer also won the British Orienteering Championships in 1991 and 1999.
He now lives in Borlänge, Sweden.
